[A photo of russules may be found at:
<http://topvaness.unblog.fr/tag/russules/>
A photo of a death cap may be found at:
<http://www.anbg.gov.au/fungi/deathcap.html>
A photo of _Armillaria mellea_ may be seen at:
<http://www.mykoweb.com/CAF/species/Armillaria_mellea.html>
Photos of _Paxillus involutus_ may be seen at:
<http://www.biopix.dk/Species.asp?Language=la&Searchtext=Paxillus%20involutus&Category=Svampe>
Most of these mushrooms have an initial resemblance to each other.
However there are subtle but specific differences that most people do
not key in on. It may be as little as the difference in spore sizes.
- Mod.TG]
